\begin{theorem}
Explicitly, if $f\colon G\to\trivialGroup$ is a group morphism and $g\in G$,
then $f(g)=1$ is the identity element.
\end{theorem}

<<Theorem: if $f\colon G\to\trivialGroup$ and $g\in G$, then $f(g)=1$>>=
